			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You'll get screwed on commission sure.  But you should get base salary even without a time clock.  If you are on salary there is no law that says you have to work at least 40 hours to get that salary.  Phone records, business related e-mail on specific dates, etc, all can establish you were doing your job.
<br />

<br />
But if you are in some crazy 100% commission job, you need to keep some serious hard charger personal records on every sale you make or yes you will get screwed.
<br />

<br />
My personal favorite is when a Sales finally lands that huge account, and instead of paying him commission on when the product ships, they just fire him so they can keep those extra points.  You're right, the labor board won't get involved in a case like that, you would need to litigate it civilly.  But this wasn't the case Zac was describing.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
