<br />
Actually in some states like Ca"li" fornia (liberal.. hehe)  they use an average wage for protecting the employee. 
<br />

<br />
So if an employee's base is $200 a week and they make 10% comission on everything they sell and in the last 52 weeks they sold 500K worth of goods. The labor board would "assume" on behalf of the employee that they make $1161 per week gross (if the agreement is salary plus commission)  or they would make $961 per week gross (if they are working on a $200 base or commission).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639739" target="_blank" class="postlink">Danille Impholder</a>
