			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, make sure you your name off that joint account.  Because once the legal actions start (and they will start) if your name is on anything jointly with her (unless a contract specifically states the break down in the joint venture) you will be held also to pay back the money.
<br />

<br />
Second, have you been living with this person? and how long have you been together?  Check out your states laws on community property and length of time before Common Law Spouse rights come into effect.
<br />

<br />
Third, start looking for a lawyer for yourself, not just her,  as you also went on the vacation, you can now be seen as an accomplis to the crime, if the Company desides to bring charges against your girlfriend.
<br />

<br />
Last, I would remove this person from your life as much as possible,  while she may have a problem with spending and in need of some profesional help.  You are in great danger of being seen as part of this and may even end up with a criminal record (this being extreme) to having your own wages garnished to pay all this back.
<br />

<br />
edit: just saw the post above, the owner of the company is getting himself in a bind by telling everyone about this.  Eventhough your girlfriend may have done this.  As an employer this is all strictly confidential until there is any legal taken.  As of right now your girlfriend could go to the local labor rights board and claim that he is smearing her name as there has been no legal action taken. 
<br />

<br />
ALL pending legal actions are personal and confidential and are not to be discussed outside of the Company and HR department.
<br />

<br />
He has the right to tell employees and subcontractors that she was removed from the company and not to deal with her about company business that is it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Good luck,  I think you are going to need it
<br />

<br />
Nitra</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
